                            <comment id="386940" author="JIRAUSER17312" created="Fri, 22 Sep 2023 21:38:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you have a specific layout defined, dsync from mpifileutils can be leveraged to copy into these targets.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="386351" author="JIRAUSER18707" created="Mon, 18 Sep 2023 21:04:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the link. I checked mpifileutils but only saw that it can be used to migrate from one lustre to another lustre. What I need is a fast approach to migrate files from a bunch of retiring OSTs to other active OSTs. Is there a way to do it using mpifileutils? If yes, how to do it?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jane&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="385512" author="JIRAUSER17312" created="Mon, 11 Sep 2023 17:22:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://hpc.github.io/mpifileutils/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hpc.github.io/mpifileutils/&lt;/a&gt; might be a useful tool for this task and help speed up your migration dramatically.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
